  "device": "AC",
  "notes": [
    "Source: IRDB (github.com/probonopd/irdb) \u2014 codes/Samsung/Air Conditioner/1,8.csv",
    "Protocol: Samsung20 (proprietary 20-bit pulse-distance, device=1 subdevice=8).",
    "Stored as raw timing arrays in microseconds because our firmware's IRremoteESP8266",
    "build does not expose a named Samsung20 encoder \u2014 raw fallback works the same.",
    "These are stateless single-button codes from an older Samsung remote (ARH-700-style).",
    "Modern split/inverter Samsung ACs use a stateful 56-bit protocol that cannot be",
    "expressed this way \u2014 for those, capture each setting via the learn flow instead.",
    "Carrier: 38 kHz, base unit: 564us.",
    "Coverage: power, mode_cool, mode_fan, fan_speed (cycles), temp_up, temp_down, swing, sleep.",
    "Other slots (mode_heat/dry/auto, fan_low/med/high/auto, timer) intentionally left empty",
    "because the IRDB capture didn't include them."
  ],
